<br>
Tried a naked pet (BOIII and DS) and a cheeta ripped through him pretty good (pet went down to one bubble of life) I had to nuke and heal the pet during the fight.<br>
<br>
Next I loaded the pet with the following:<br>
summoned armor (all pieces)<br>
2 Summoned Daggers<br>
1 elemental defender (equiped as a back piece)<br>
2 Focus earrings<br>
2 focus necklaces (thought I read someplace there are 2 neck slots, shrug)<br>
2 focus rings<br>
<br>
Pet never went below 2 bubbles of life and I could use my BWS as opposed to chain nuking and healing the pet to keep him alive.<br>
<br>
I didn't test for any cast time reduction or increase of damage.  Best to dual someone to test that out.  Might give that a whirl tonight. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugreldek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Greldek</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#333333>(8/23/02 12:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=639.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.newgumbrea.com/images/ico-gruffi.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pet and Summoned Focus items</span><hr size=1> I've been giving my pet 1 summoned dmg bracer, and a elemental defender for back, and an almost full suit of summoned leather (minus 1 bracer)<br>
